(1) Commissioners may— (a) enter upon and inspect any land, building, place or vessel, and inspect any goods and other things, the entry upon or inspection of which appears to them to be requisite for the purposes of the inquiry; (b) require, by summons, in the form prescribed in the Second Schedule, the attendance of any person whom they wish to call before them and call for the production of books, plans and documents; (c) examine witnesses on oath or affirmation, administered by them.
